## 6. Case Studies and Real-World Examples

### 6.1 Dupray (Montreal-based Manufacturer)

Dupray manages currency risk through internal forecasting and futures contracts, reducing exposure by hedging approximately 50% of their currency risk. Their diversified currency exposure acts as a natural hedge, absorbing fluctuations across CAD, EUR, and USD ([FXcompared, 2022](https://www.fxcompared.com/magazine/foreign-exchange-risk)).

### 6.2 EverBamboo (Natural Products Company)

EverBamboo mitigates currency risk by invoicing customers in USD and negotiating prices to accommodate currency fluctuations, using currency specialists for better rates than banks ([FXcompared, 2022](https://www.fxcompared.com/magazine/foreign-exchange-risk)).

